node.text:
4 DAYS UNTIL SELFHEALERS CIRCLE ENROLLMENT 🎉

Thanks to member feedback, we’ve spent the past year building our own hosting platform. It’s easier to navigate + we now have a private community outside of facebook. Members are loving our new space.

The cost is $26/month or $286/year (one month free). My goal has always been to make the Circle affordable + accessible.

Enrollment will open January 1st at 12pm PST. Spaces are limited + do SELL OUT quickly. If you’re on the waitlist, you’ll be sent a link a few moments before enrollment opens. It might be helpful to set an alarm. There are currently 30,000+ people on the waitlist.

To find complete details on what the circle is all about, click the link in my bio. You can also add yourself to the waitlist.

I’ll see you in the ⭕️ + cannot wait for your healing journey to begin! selfhealers

node.text: Today it’s a true honor to talk to @dr.editheger— I’m actually a bit overwhelmed post filming this. Edith is a psychologist + Holocaust survivor who just released the book “The Gift.” I got chills throughout the book + know members of this community will love every word. Edith is an embodied teacher who gifts us with the wisdom that we are not not victims of our past, but powerful creators of our future. Her story is a testament to our true human potential. She’s a gift. I hope you all enjoy #selfhealers

node.title: Holocaust Survivor + Author Dr. Edith Edger

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Why a Conscious Society Will Change Our World @the.holistic.psychologist SWIPE LEFT'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Values of Unconscious Society @the.holistic.psychologist Achieve produce: glorify 'busyness', impress others, career is self worth Materialism: endless consumption, financial success over happiness, hoarding of resources, human beings are disposable Competition: isn't room for everyone, tear down tactics, "me' comes first, domination Elitism: knowledge, access, availability to select few, "experts' know all Focus on physical: Ûbssion with body image, agism, fear of growing old Homogenization: everything/everyone is uniform or the same, intolerance, speaking for entire groups of people'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Values of Conscious Society @the.holistic. @the.holistic.psychologist Create: make what you love what moves you, contribute, follow your unique interests Self Connection: validation comes from how you feel about yourself, not the external or societa expectations Collaboration:you winning means can too, uplift others, encourage others, create together, trust in your own process Access: knowledge, availability to ALL. Life experiences valued, resources shared Focus on the spiritual: aware of the nnate interconnected nature of life. Tolerance, Uniqueness differences are celebrated, trust in other, loving awareness'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'From the time we are children, we are sent to school where we learn the following: we must compete against others, 'failure'/ mistakes are bad, our grades are linked to self worth, information or access IS only available if 'achieve (ex-college acceptance), don't question authority, my true talents aren't worth developing, play it safe. @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Every day we are evaluated by how we perform in that process we learn to look to others to tell us our ranking, how we are perceived, w”ajobs or roles are worthy of going after. This is the foundation of an unconscious society (people disconnected from their true nature.) @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Many of us spend ad”lthood chasing the perfect job, perfect house, perfect spouse, pleasing our parents, pleasing the neighbors, unaware that we have beliefs+ drives that have been conditioned within us (that we did not consciously choose.) @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'This is the path to suffering, to resentment, to not feeling worthy. Not because we aren't worthy, but because we are sleep walking through life: checkino boxes, numbing out, practicing chronic escapism, + feeling insecure throughout the process. @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'When people are insecure they do the following: hoard resources, exclude others, cheat to 'get ahead' (an illusion), feel threatened by uniqueness or differentness, make decisions based on what's best for "me" rather than what's best for "we." @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'We do this until we are so miserable (suffer So deeply) that we wake up or become conscious. This is a warriors journey because becoming conscious means: facing your shame, learning to forgive yourself, witnessing your parents as human beings, having the humility to unlearn relearn. @the.holistic.psychologist'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 03, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'With every person who becomes conscious, we form a new world built on:collaboration, creativity, unity, acceptance, trust, curiosity, we each remember who we actually are. We say goodbye to an unconscious society that subscibes to: control, shaming, fear tactics, intolerance, division, + ego based behaviors. @the.holistic.psychologist'.

When you choose a relationship of evolution, you’re choosing to view your relationship as a space for freedom + mutual evolution. Not as a space to be ‘completed’, to play a role, or to enable.

This a process + a conscious choice to meet self + another. It’s a spiritual choice to unlearn conditioned patterns + unhealthy dynamics to actually let your authentic self unfold while being fully witnessed— by another.

Which stage are you in? #selfhealers

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stage One: idolization ntense thought patterns of the other person + +physical hormonal release (dopamine, oxytocin) within the body. Partners see the "best" in each other +the mystery of it all is all consuming. @the.holistic.psychologist Inner Child Response: childhood fantasies come flooding in EX: (I'll finally be chosen, this person will rescue me, this person will love me unconditionally like a parent did not, this person is "perfect")'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stage Two: Grounding partners begin steady life together navigate conflict, day to day experiences make commitments, meet each others (ego/ (ego/coping mechanisms) become aware of each others patterns. @the.holistic.psychologist Inner Child Response: fear of abandonment, being seen, of commitment, fear of losing autonomy/singl life, excitement around building a life together, excitement around having a person to share life with.'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stage Three: Grief + Mourning partners begin to witness each others flaws activate each others childhood traumas. Disappointment around the partners "fall from grace" which can cause fear based reactions like: rebelling acting out, shutting down, causing conflict, 'ghosting." @the.holistic.psychologist Inner Child Response: mourns independence, fantasies about past partners or of who else is 'out there ego can become very fragile in this stage begin to focus solely on partners perceived flaws.'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stage Four: Acceptance partners make a conscious choice to view relationships as spaces for mutual freedom + evolution. Unconscious control, unhealthy dynamics can still be present but partners have a willingness to heal together. They forgives themselves + each other freely. @the.holistic.psychologist Inner Child Response: feels more safe, seen, + able to self express. Also feels bored/trapped + attempts to hide often. Needs to re-learn security, peace, + lack of chaos as healthy relationship dynamic.'.

Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 02, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Stage Five: A Trust in Freedom partners trust themselves other to do/know what's best for themselves. Both know they are loved (for who they actually are), can depend on each other know the role they have in each other lives. Vulnerability, compassion, grace are centered over perfection. Curiosity exists over shame. Stability predictability are valued as a sign of growth, not as 'lack of passion.' @the.holistic.psychologist Inner Child Response: healing from new found trust, new dynamics, acceptance + awareness of each others childhood trauma. Fear unhealthy coping still comes up, its just related to differently.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on September 01, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'What is Codependency? @the.holistic.psychologist SWIPELEFT SWIPE LEFT'.

node.text:
Codependent relationships are so normalized + common we usually aren’t even aware of the dynamics.

I know I wasn’t.

My childhood conditioning created dynamics where I had to deny my own needs. I had to focus on the emotions of everyone else around me. My dad would have emotional outbursts, my mom would completely shut down + withdraw. And, my parents (not understanding their own emotions) couldn’t give me the emotional attunement to help me get through my ‘big’ feelings. 

So, I became responsible for theirs.

Then, I became responsible for the emotions of everyone I dated. This is what I knew. My needs had no place. 

Then, I would blame my partners. They’re not emotionally available. They aren’t giving me what I want. They don’t actually see me (do they even LIKE me?) 

This damaged my relationships, but most importantly, it damaged my relationship with myself.

I’ve been on a journey of healing from this for years. I still struggle with what’s “mine” + what’s someone else’s. Still cringe with guilt over saying ‘no’ or not appeasing (my go-to state.) 

And I’m learning.

I’m unwinding years of conditioning to create space for me. To put my needs first— which had made me a better partner + has allowed me to trade some long term guilt for joy.

Do you notice codependent relationships in your own life? #selfhealers

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Dr. Nicole LePera on August 31, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'The more comfortable you are with your own "human-ness" the more comfortable you are with someone else's @the.holistic.psychologist'.

node.text:
Recently, I’ve been thinking about my own journey. So much has changed for me in the past couple of years. And all of those changes come from this community— from your insane level of support.

I made a promise to myself that my message would always stay pure. That I would never say yes to any situation where I would have to shift my message, downplay it, or change it. That I would create a level integrity, transparency, + trust with my community. That I would leave money on the table + say no any time anything felt slightly out of alignment. That I would make as much content as I can completely free— +  produce everything myself so that that content came without ads or messaging that would require me to betray myself.

In the past few years I’ve had extreme highs + extreme lows. Lived some really tough lessons. Saw people I trusted use my name to twist my message. I’ve picked myself up over + over again. Mostly because there are people around the world healing from this work. People whose lives are the living testament that we can heal ourselves. 

A message that not everyone wants you to hear.

It’s funny because what I used to sit and visualize/journal about years ago is now my reality. Without a publicist, a manager, without mainstream media, celebrity endorsements— without investments. Without ever spending a dime on advertising. 

This became a movement.

I got here because of YOU. And that is something that fuels me to create more, to give me, to show up, to breathe through all of the fear. 

Anyway, thank you. Thank you for sharing my work. For supporting what I create. For pushing me + challenging me. For writing me the most kind, thoughtful DMs. For seeing the truth in what I teach. For commenting on my posts. For doing this work because you are changing this world.

Thank you. I’m here because of you. And so we keep going #selfhealers

node.text:
1. Being triggered can be a positive thing— it can lead to expanding your mind + deepening awareness 

2. Disagreement is healthy. Agreeing to disagree takes a level of emotional maturity. 

3. Hero worshipping or guru chasing is just a sign that you’re struggling to see that everything you want “out there” is within YOU.

4. Human beings are flawed. No one knows what they’re actually doing. No ones perfect. We all have a deep dark belief that we might not be worthy.

5. We project onto others what we want to avoid in ourselves— wise people pay attention to what/how they project 

6. Being confused on what to think, who to believe, or feeling completely overwhelmed is the beginning of finding YOUR OWN voice.

7. Conflicting emotions will come up almost every day. Most people shut down, dissociate, or act out when this happens. If you can learn to sit with the discomfort, you’ll learn just how resilient you are.

8. Black + white thinking is a trauma response— it protects us from the unknown, but the unknown is where we grow. (Read this twice)

9. The more comfortable you are with your ‘human-ness’ the more comfortable you are with someone else’s.

10. Most people’s intentions are pure— keep this in mind when your ego starts to create stories about a persons “why.” These stories have more to do with your own past than the present moment #selfhealers

node.text:
Outrage culture sells. And it’s selling in a big way right now.

This is because it’s addictive. 

The hormonal responses in the body + the pull of our ego to feel superior is seductive. Every day can become an emotional roller coaster where we feel more + more angry + less able to focus our energy on things that serve us. At the same time it is also the only time we actually *feel* which can make us come back for more + more because the fleeting emotions of outrage feel better than feeling nothing at all.

When we exist within outrage culture, we exist in survival mode. The primitive “lizard” part of our brain is dominate which leads to knee-jerk reactions, impulsivity, + self neglect.

The physical/mental affects are: brain fog fatigue, inability to think logically, indecisiveness, memory issues, + high emotional reactivity (or complete shut down.)

To heal, we must become conscious to what we consume, how we behave, + face the reality of what our beliefs do for our own ego. This takes a lot of radical honesty.

As we heal we have more access to our pre-frontal cortex. The part of our brain that allows for creativity, solutions, rational thinking, connection, collaboration.

In short: we leave the righteous ego self (survival mode) for the self that is able to make impact + create meaningful change.

We also become more confident, more in control of our emotional states, + more empathetic tolerate to ideas beyond our limited perspective.

Do you notice outrage culture in your life? #selfhealers
